Leke Adeboye, son of the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG), Pastor Enoch Adeboye, has stated that he is waiting for critics to come for the upcoming commissioning of a dialysis centre at the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa Teaching Hospital, Bauchi. The senior personal assistant to the General Overseer disclosed this on Thursday in a post via his Facebook page, announcing that Adeboye and his wife, Pastor Folu will inaugurate the Enoch and Folu Adeboye Dialysis Centre, ATBU, Bauchi, on Friday, February 18, 2022. “I am waiting for the criticism on this one,” he wrote, posting a flyer of the event on his page. Adeboye Releases Eight Prophecies For 2022 I Can Never Minister Where Malicious Words Are Said About… The inauguration of the centre is in commemoration of the General Overseer’s 80th birthday, on March 2, 2022. The Dialysis Centre which was built by the charity arm of the church, His Love Foundation, has dialysis machines, a 30KVA generator, and medical water reverse osmosis purification system.